 10 Infinity Mountains, Fujian Province 

00:00:06.841 --> 00:00:12.649
 This UNESCO world heritage is the largest and richest subtropical forest ecosystem in Central Asia. 

00:00:12.756 --> 00:00:18.465
 Admission fee: US $ 22 (1 day); US $ 24 (two days); US $ 26 (3 days) 

00:00:18.571 --> 00:00:21.725
 9 Tam Khong Temple in Khuc City, Shandong Province 

00:00:21.845 --> 00:00:34.849
 The birthplace of Confucius is also on the UNESCO world heritage list. There are 3 main areas, including Khong Tu Temple, Khong Phu and Khong Lam 

00:00:34.969 --> 00:00:38.317
 Admission price: US $ 30 

00:00:38.441 --> 00:00:41.213
 8 Golden Dragon Scenic Area, Sichuan 

00:00:41.354 --> 00:00:47.952
 The main attraction of tourists is the Golden Dragon Valley, located under the highest peak of the Man Son mountain range 

00:00:48.083 --> 00:00:53.760
 It is famous for its beautiful colorful lakes, snowy peaks, deep canyons, and dense forests. 

00:00:53.895 --> 00:01:00.269
 As the residence of some endangered animals, such as giant panda, Monkey upturned nose Sichuan. 

00:01:00.400 --> 00:01:03.515
 Admission price: US $ 33 

00:01:03.632 --> 00:01:06.647
 7 Potala Palace, Lhasa, Tibet 

00:01:06.760 --> 00:01:13.517
 The Potala Palace was once the residence of Dalai Lama until he ran to Dharamsala, India due to the Tibetan 1959 uprising. 

00:01:13.617 --> 00:01:22.900
 To preserve the Potala palace, every day it sells only 2,300 tickets, and during peak travel times, you will need to buy tickets in advance one day. 

00:01:23.042 --> 00:01:26.408
 Admission fee: US $ 16 (guest season); US $ 32 (high season) 

00:01:27.438 --> 00:01:29.894
 6 Nine Camp Valley, Sichuan 

00:01:29.994 --> 00:01:40.813
 The valley with magical blue lakes, waterfalls, dense forests and snowy peaks, is named after the 9 Tibetan villages surrounding it. 

00:01:40.913 --> 00:01:44.271
 Admission fee: US $ 13 (empty season); US $ 35 (high season) 

00:01:44.406 --> 00:01:47.202
 5 Wudang Mountain, Hubei Province 

00:01:47.308 --> 00:01:57.067
 From the Tang Dynasty (618-907), this land was regarded as the cradle of Taoism. Therefore, many Taoist schools are well preserved here. 

00:01:57.167 --> 00:02:05.639
 Famous buildings and monasteries such as the Golden Floor, Nam Nham Temple and Temple of Purple Clouds have become UNESCO world heritage sites in 1994. 

00:02:05.747 --> 00:02:12.620
 Wudang Mountain has a deep relationship with Master Zhang Tam Feng, founder of Wudang and Tai Chi. 

00:02:12.720 --> 00:02:16.806
 Admission price: US $ 38 

00:02:16.928 --> 00:02:19.014
 4 Golden Mountains, Anhui Province 

00:02:19.114 --> 00:02:31.565
 Considered one of the most famous mountains in China, Golden Mountain is famous for its scenery, sunset, granite peaks protruding, Golden Mountain pine trees and the cloudy mountain scenery over 200 days in year. 

00:02:31.665 --> 00:02:41.315
 In addition to being portrayed in all forms of ancient Chinese art, the Avatar blockbuster also sees Gold Mountain as a model that has a great influence on the fictional world in the film. 

00:02:41.415 --> 00:02:43.983
 Admission price: 230RMB, $ 38US 

00:02:45.473 --> 00:02:46.972
 3 Zhangjiajie, Hunan Province 

00:02:47.082 --> 00:02:56.845
 In 1982, Zhangjiajie became the first National Forest Park of China, and in 1992, Wuyi Yuan Scenic Area was selected as a UNESCO World Heritage Site. 

00:02:56.990 --> 00:03:00.217
 Admission price: US $ 40 

